{
  "text": "The Beaver Dam Eye Study (BDES) recently found a higher prevalence of 26% (551 of 1540 eyes) of VMA. [CITATION_1] However, subjects were younger than in the ALIENOR Study (mean age ALIENOR: 82.2 years [SD: 4.3 years] compared with a mean age of 74.1 years [SD: 7.1 years] in BDES). This result is consistent with the decline in the prevalence of VMA in the oldest old, as shown in our study.",
